dfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/WPML-and-Enfold-150x38.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/WPML-and-Enfold-300x76.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/WPML-and-Enfold.png 689w" sizes="(max-width: 689px) 100vw, 689px" /></h3>\n<h3><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Introduction</strong></span></h3>\n<p>Enfold theme allows you to build a website in a few minutes. It includes many features, and can be optimized based on your needs. It also comes with predefined content for easy setup.</p>\n<p>Enfold’s integration with WPML allows you to translate your pages, posts, menus, custom post types, and all the other theme elements. You can read more about it, download, and look at the multilingual test site here: <a href="https://wpml.org/theme/enfold/">https://wpml.org/theme/enfold/</a></p>\n<p>In this documentation, we provide detailed instructions on how to translate the different elements of Enfold’s theme using WPML.</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>What you will need</strong></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>The <a href="http://www.kriesi.at/documentation/enfold/downloads/">Enfold Theme</a>, which is also available on <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/enfold-responsive-multipurpose-theme/4519990">Theme Forest</a> (version 3.3 or above).</li>\n<li>A recent version of <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/">WPML</a> (version 3.3.6 or above), including the String Translation, Translation Management, and Media translation add-ons.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Essential resources</strong></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://www.kriesi.at/documentation/enfold/">Enfold documentation</a> has a rich collection of tutorials and step-by-step videos that will guide you in your initial setup.</li>\n<li>The WPML <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/">Getting Started Guide</a> contains clear explanations of many of the steps involved in turning an Enfold site multilingual with WPML. You will want to refer later to some of its subtopics, such as Theme and Plugin Localization, Menu Synchronization, and String Translation. We recommend you keep this guide open while following this tutorial.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Content</strong></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="#1">Getting started</a> | installing and activating Enfold theme, importing content, and setting up WPML plugin</li>\n<li><a href="#2">Translating pages created with the page builder</a> | includes translating the home page</li>\n<li><a href="#3">Translating pages, posts, custom post types and custom taxonomies</a> | portfolio, portfolio categories</li>\n<li><a href="#4">Translating menus</a> | synchronize menus across languages and translate them</li>\n<li><a href="#5">Translating theme text</a> | scan your theme for strings and get everything translated</li>\n<li><a href="#6">Translating theme options</a> | using the theme option language switcher</li>\n<li><a href="#7">Getting help</a> | our support team will be more than happy to assist you</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id="1"><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Getting started</strong></span></h3>\n<p>These are the main steps you need to follow to get started:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install the Enfold theme and activate it.</li>\n<li>Install and activate the core WPML plugins (WPML Multilingual CMS, WPML String Translation, WPML Translation Management, WPML Media Translation), and then other WPML plugins that may depend on them.</li>\n<li>Set up WPML,  See our WPML <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/">Getting Started Guide</a> for a complete reference, but the initial simple three-step setup is self-explanatory, asking you to choose your default language, a set of active languages, and a language selector. (For starters, choose the footer language selector; you can change this later.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For this tutorial, we will use some of the sample content available in Enfold theme. You can import this content by going to <strong>Enfold,</strong> clicking on the <strong>Demo Import</strong> tab on the left, then clicking on the <strong>Click to import </strong>button as illustrated below.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/import-demo-content.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820184" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/import-demo-content-300x183.png" alt="import demo content" width="421" height="257" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/import-demo-content-300x183.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/import-demo-content-768x468.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/import-demo-content.png 1021w" sizes="(max-width: 421px) 100vw, 421px" /></a></p>\n<h3 style="text-align: left"><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Translating theme elements</strong></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li style="text-align: left">\n<h3 id="2"><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong><span style="color: #6a9db6">Tr</span>anslating pages created with the page builder</strong></span></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="text-align: left">When you navigate to “Pages” in the WordPress dashboard you will see columns for each active language, with the <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-820189" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/image2.png" alt="plus" width="16" height="16" />  icon (add a translation) or the <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-820192" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/image3.png" alt="pencil" width="17" height="16" /> icon (edit translation) next to each page. Go ahead and edit or add the translated page for “Homepage.”</p>\n<p>The homepage downloaded by the demo content is built using the <em>Advanced layout editor</em>. If you are using Enfold’s <em>Advanced layout editor</em> to create your own homepage or any other page, follow the steps below for translation:</p>\n<p><strong><em>Note that</em></strong><em> the </em>Advanced layout editor<em> is a page layout builder that allows you to design and modify the layout as well as add functionality inside a single page and view from within the admin of that page.</em></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to Pages.</li>\n<li>Find your home page.</li>\n<li>Click on <strong>Edit</strong> as shown in the illustration below.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-homepage.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820200" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-homepage-300x165.png" alt="translate homepage" width="438" height="241" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-homepage-300x165.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-homepage-768x422.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-homepage-1024x562.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-homepage.png 1133w" sizes="(max-width: 438px) 100vw, 438px" /></a></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">4. You will see the language meta box on the right side. Check the <strong>Duplicate</strong> option, and then click on the <strong>Duplicate</strong> button, as shown in the illustration below.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/duplicate-translation-.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820204" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/duplicate-translation--300x135.png" alt="duplicate translation" width="469" height="211" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/duplicate-translation--300x135.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/duplicate-translation--768x346.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/duplicate-translation--1024x461.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/duplicate-translation-.png 1339w" sizes="(max-width: 469px) 100vw, 469px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="5">\n<li>Click on the <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-820192" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/image3.png" alt="pencil" width="17" height="16" /> icon to go to the secondary language home page as shown in the illustration below.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-translation-.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820209 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-translation-.png" alt="add translation" width="271" height="206" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-translation--150x114.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-translation-.png 271w" sizes="(max-width: 271px) 100vw, 271px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="6">\n<li>Click on the <strong>Translate independently</strong> button to disconnect the page’s translations.</li>\n<li>Edit the text for translation.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>With that, we have created a copy of our homepage in the secondary language and can add the translated content to it.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<h3 id="3"><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Translating pages, posts, custom post types, and custom taxonomies</strong></span></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Translating pages and posts can be done by navigating to Pages or Posts on the WordPress dashboard and clicking on the <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-820189" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/image2.png" alt="plus" width="16" height="16" /> icon to add the translated content to the secondary language.</p>\n<p>As you can see, the custom post that comes with Enfold theme, like “Portfolio,” and the custom taxonomy, like “Portfolio Categories,” are preset to be translated by the language configuration file, which we have created for Enfold theme.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to “Portfolio items” in your WordPress dashboard and click on the <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-820189" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/image2.png" alt="plus" width="16" height="16" /> icon to add the translation. See the illustration below:</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-items.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820224 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-items-300x136.png" alt="translate portfolio items" width="488" height="221" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-items-150x68.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-items-300x136.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-items-768x349.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-items-1024x465.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-items.png 1158w" sizes="(max-width: 488px) 100vw, 488px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="2">\n<li>To translate the custom taxonomies, follow the steps below:</li>\n</ol>\n<p style="padding-left: 60px">A. Go to WPML <strong>&gt;&gt; </strong>Taxonomy Translation.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 60px">B. Select “Portfolio Categories” from the <strong>Select the taxonomy to translate</strong> drop-down menu.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 60px">C. Click on <strong>Translate</strong> to add the custom taxonomy translation by filling the required fields and then click <strong>OK</strong> as illustrated below.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 60px"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-pategories.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820227" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-pategories-300x137.png" alt="translate portfolio pategories" width="532" height="243" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-pategories-300x137.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-pategories-768x352.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-pategories-1024x469.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-portfolio-pategories.png 1326w" sizes="(max-width: 532px) 100vw, 532px" /></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<h3 id="4"><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Translating Menus</strong></span></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>WPML can synchronize menus for you. This means that if some entries, for example some pages, posts, or categories, are in the English menu, WPML can generate and keep in sync menus for other languages pointing to the translated versions of these pages, posts, or categories. By following the steps below you will be able to synchronize the menus and translate them.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>From WordPress Appearance <strong>&gt;&gt;</strong> Menus, click on <strong>Synchronize menus between languages</strong> as shown in the illustration below:</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Synchronize-menus-between-languages.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820232 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Synchronize-menus-between-languages-300x131.png" alt="Synchronize menus between languages" width="474" height="207" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Synchronize-menus-between-languages-300x131.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Synchronize-menus-between-languages-768x336.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Synchronize-menus-between-languages-1024x448.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Synchronize-menus-between-languages.png 1342w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="2">\n<li>Now you are directed to a page that shows the menu items available for translation. Scroll to the end of the page and click the <strong>Sync</strong> button, as shown in the illustration below:</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sync-button-.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820238" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sync-button--300x208.png" alt="sync button" width="480" height="333" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sync-button--150x104.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sync-button--300x208.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sync-button--768x533.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sync-button-.png 874w" sizes="(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="3">\n<li>Clicking the <strong>Sync</strong> button will take you to the set of menu items that can be translated; select them all, then apply the changes.</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<h3 id="5"><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Translating theme text and other strings on your website</strong></span></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Scanning the theme strings will register them for translation on the string translation screen. Learn more at <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/">Theme and Plugin Localization</a>.</p>\n<p>This can be done by following the steps below:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to WPML <strong>&gt;&gt; </strong>Theme and plugin localization.</li>\n<li>Click on the <strong>Scan the theme for strings</strong> This will register the theme texts for translation on the string translation screen, as shown in the illustration below.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/scan-the-theme-for-strings.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820240" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/scan-the-theme-for-strings-300x93.png" alt="scan the theme for strings" width="526" height="163" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/scan-the-theme-for-strings-300x93.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/scan-the-theme-for-strings-768x239.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/scan-the-theme-for-strings-1024x319.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/scan-the-theme-for-strings.png 1329w" sizes="(max-width: 526px) 100vw, 526px" /></a></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">3. Now you can navigate to WPML &gt;&gt; String translation, and filter the strings by “translation needed” to see which strings are missing translations or select a specific text domain. You also can search for a specific string by typing it in the “Search for” field and clicking the <strong>Search</strong> button. Click on <strong>translations</strong> and add your translated text, as shown in the illustration below.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-page.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820242 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-page-300x136.png" alt="string translation page" width="531" height="241" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-page-150x68.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-page-300x136.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-page-768x348.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-page-1024x463.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-page.png 1328w" sizes="(max-width: 531px) 100vw, 531px" /></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li style="padding-left: 30px">\n<h3 id="6"><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Translating theme options</strong></span></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can simply translate the theme options by following the steps below:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to Enfold settings on your WordPress dashboard.</li>\n<li>Click on the options tab on the left.</li>\n<li>Use the language switcher on the theme options page located on the top left corner to switch between the default language and the secondary language(s).</li>\n</ol>\n<p>With that you can edit the translation of the theme options under each language as shown in the illustration below.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-theme-options.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-820248 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-theme-options-300x174.png" alt="translate theme options" width="502" height="291" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-theme-options-150x87.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-theme-options-300x174.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-theme-options-768x446.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-theme-options-1024x594.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-theme-options.png 1049w" sizes="(max-width: 502px) 100vw, 502px" /></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<h3 id="7"><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Getting help</strong></span></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you need help with using WPML with Enfold theme, please go to our <a href="https://wpml.org/forums/forum/english-support/">technical forum</a>. Before posting about issues, we recommend that you review this quick checklist:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Make sure you have the latest versions of the theme and of the WPML plugins, and that they are all activated. These include WPML Multilingual CMS, WPML String Translation, and WPML Translation Management.</li>\n<li>The problem does not appear if the WPML plugins are deactivated; it appears when only the core WPML plugins are activated. In other words, try to make sure that it is an issue of compatibility of Enfold with WPML, because otherwise Enfold support is likely to be able to help you better.</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<h3 id="8"><span style="color: #6a9db6"><strong>Conclusion</strong></span></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Enfold theme has many features; with WPML integration you will be able to easily translate all its different elements. The detailed instructions introduced in this document will allow you to build your localized website smartly using Enfold theme and WPML.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=Pg_4ksUKZx0:8Ztpbf2ixlo:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=Pg_4ksUKZx0:8Ztpbf2ixlo:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=Pg_4ksUKZx0:8Ztpbf2ixlo:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=Pg_4ksUKZx0:8Ztpbf2ixlo:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=Pg_4ksUKZx0:8Ztpbf2ixlo:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=Pg_4ksUKZx0:8Ztpbf2ixlo:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/Pg_4ksUKZx0" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:52:"https://wpml.org/2016/02/enfold-theme-and-wpml/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"https://wpml.org/2016/02/enfold-theme-and-wpml/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"Content Aware Sidebars &amp; WPML";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/nm8j8Un8RVs/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"https://wpml.org/2016/02/content-aware-sidebars-wpml/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 17 Feb 2016 11:34:50 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Compatibility";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=812533";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:352:"Introduction The Content Aware Sidebars plugin lets you create an infinite number of custom sidebars and assign them to widgets based on the language of the contents on the page. The integration of Content Aware Sidebars with WPML allows you to set different sidebars for content in different languages. After collaborating with the author of [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Mohamed Khafaja";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15925:"<h3><span style="color: #5b94af"><strong>Introduction</strong></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/content-aware-sidebars/">Content Aware Sidebars</a> plugin lets you create an infinite number of custom sidebars and assign them to widgets based on the language of the contents on the page.</p>\n<p>The integration of Content Aware Sidebars with WPML allows you to set different sidebars for content in different languages.</p>\n<p>After collaborating with the author of Content Aware Sidebars, we managed to translate all the strings coming from the plugin<strong>.</strong></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #5b94af"><strong>What you will need:</strong></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A recent version of <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/">WPML</a> along with <a href="https://wpml.org/download/wpml-string-translation/">String Translation</a> and <a href="https://wpml.org/download/wpml-translation-management/">Translation Management </a>add-ons.</li>\n<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/content-aware-sidebars/">Content Aware Sidebars</a> (version 3.1.1 or above).</li>\n<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpml-widgets/">WPML Widgets</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #5b94af"><strong>Essential resources:</strong></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>WPML’s <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/">Getting Started Guide</a> will guide you on how to easily setup WPML; you may also want to refer to the <a href="https://wpml.org/2014/08/display-different-widgets-per-language-wpml-widgets/">WPML Widgets documentation</a>.</li>\n<li><a href="http://www.intox.dk/en/plugin/content-aware-sidebars-en/faq/">Content Aware Sidebars FAQs</a> will help you with the setup.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style="color: #5b94af"><strong>Creating different custom sidebars for different languages with Content Aware Sidebars and WPML</strong></span></h3>\n<p>Before going into details, a summary of the 7 steps to be followed to translate the Content Aware Sidebar plugin outputs is as follows:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Set WPML to register custom posts obtained from the Content Aware Sidebars for translation.</li>\n<li>Add a new sidebar to the default language.</li>\n<li>Add the custom posts to the translation basket.</li>\n<li>Choose whether the custom posts are to be translated by a local translator or a professional translation service.</li>\n<li>Translate the custom posts (by a local translator).</li>\n<li>Add a new sidebar for the secondary language.</li>\n<li>Assign widgets to the sidebars created based on the language of the page on which the sidebars are to be displayed.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Let us start translating the Content Aware Sidebar plugin output by following the detailed steps shown below:</p>\n<p>1- Go to <strong>WPML &gt; Translation management &gt; Multilingual Content Setup,</strong> scroll down to the Custom posts section, and select the “translate” option for “Condition Groups” and “Sidebars.”</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translate-condition-groups-and-sidebars-.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812536" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translate-condition-groups-and-sidebars--300x190.png" alt="Translate condition groups and sidebars" width="467" height="296" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translate-condition-groups-and-sidebars--150x95.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translate-condition-groups-and-sidebars--300x190.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translate-condition-groups-and-sidebars--768x488.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translate-condition-groups-and-sidebars--1024x650.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 467px) 100vw, 467px" /></a></p>\n<p>2- Go to <strong>Sidebars &gt; Add new</strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">a. Add the sidebar for your primary language, which will be English in this case; <strong><u>note that</u> </strong>you can check if your primary language selected from your WordPress admin bar.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">b. Chose conditional logic that suits your needs from the drop down menu and click on “<strong>Save </strong>“<strong>changes</strong>” and “<strong>Publish.</strong>”</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-new-sidebar-to-primary-language.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812540" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-new-sidebar-to-primary-language-300x190.png" alt="Add new sidebar to primary language" width="471" height="298" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-new-sidebar-to-primary-language-150x95.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-new-sidebar-to-primary-language-300x190.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 471px) 100vw, 471px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Select-conditional-logic.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812541" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Select-conditional-logic-300x251.png" alt="Select conditional logic" width="425" height="355" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Select-conditional-logic-150x125.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Select-conditional-logic-300x251.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Select-conditional-logic-768x642.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Select-conditional-logic-1024x857.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Select-conditional-logic.png 1395w" sizes="(max-width: 425px) 100vw, 425px" /></a></p>\n<p>3 &#8211; Go to <strong>WPML &gt; Translation management</strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">a. Select Sidebar and Conditional Group.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">b. Click on the “<strong>Add to translation basket” </strong>button.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-to-translation-basket.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812549" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-to-translation-basket-300x190.png" alt="Add to translation basket" width="484" height="307" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-to-translation-basket-150x95.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-to-translation-basket-300x190.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-to-translation-basket-768x488.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-to-translation-basket-1024x650.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 484px) 100vw, 484px" /></a></p>\n<p>4 &#8211; Go to <strong>WPML &gt; Translation management &gt; Translation basket</strong> tab.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">a. Go to the “Choose translation options” section and choose an option from the drop down menu.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">b. Select admin (local) if you are going to do the translation yourself or learn more about setting up a <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/content-translation/">professional translation service</a>; then, click on <strong>Send all items for translation</strong>.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Send-items-for-translation.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812556" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Send-items-for-translation-300x190.png" alt="Send items for translation" width="497" height="315" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Send-items-for-translation-150x95.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Send-items-for-translation-300x190.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Send-items-for-translation-768x488.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Send-items-for-translation-1024x650.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 497px) 100vw, 497px" /></a></p>\n<p>5 &#8211; Go to <strong>WPML &gt; Translations</strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">a. Add translations for the Condition Group and Sidebar by clicking on the “<strong>Edit</strong>” button</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">b. Fill the title field with the translation of the secondary language and select “<strong>This translation is finished</strong>” and repeat the same steps for the body field. Scroll down and select “<strong>Translation of this document is complete</strong>”</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">c. Click on the “<strong>Save translation</strong>” button.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-translations-for-the-Condition-Group-and-Sidebar-.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812589" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-translations-for-the-Condition-Group-and-Sidebar--300x190.png" alt="Add translations for the Condition Group and Sidebar" width="492" height="312" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-translations-for-the-Condition-Group-and-Sidebar--150x95.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-translations-for-the-Condition-Group-and-Sidebar--300x190.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-translations-for-the-Condition-Group-and-Sidebar--768x488.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-translations-for-the-Condition-Group-and-Sidebar--1024x650.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 492px) 100vw, 492px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Save-translation.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812595" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Save-translation-300x190.png" alt="Save translation" width="472" height="299" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Save-translation-150x95.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Save-translation-300x190.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Save-translation-768x488.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Save-translation-1024x650.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 472px) 100vw, 472px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translation-of-this-document-is-complete.png"><img class="wp-image-812598 aligncenter" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translation-of-this-document-is-complete-300x188.png" alt="Translation of this document is complete" width="396" height="248" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translation-of-this-document-is-complete-150x94.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translation-of-this-document-is-complete-300x188.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translation-of-this-document-is-complete-768x482.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translation-of-this-document-is-complete-1024x643.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Translation-of-this-document-is-complete.png 1149w" sizes="(max-width: 396px) 100vw, 396px" /></a></p>\n<p>6 &#8211; Go back to <strong>Sidebars</strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">a. Click on the previously created English sidebar.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">b. Use the language switcher at the top to change the language to the desired language (secondary language); now you are on the sidebar translation page.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">c. Setup your sidebar translation and conditional logic similar to that shown in <a href="#id.hlihxl1n3v2h">step 2</a>.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sidebar-translation-and-conditional-logic-for-secondary-language.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812607 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sidebar-translation-and-conditional-logic-for-secondary-language-300x161.png" alt="sidebar translation and conditional logic for secondary language" width="393" height="211" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sidebar-translation-and-conditional-logic-for-secondary-language-300x161.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sidebar-translation-and-conditional-logic-for-secondary-language-768x412.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/sidebar-translation-and-conditional-logic-for-secondary-language.png 846w" sizes="(max-width: 393px) 100vw, 393px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Secondary-language-sidebar-translation.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812612 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Secondary-language-sidebar-translation-300x190.png" alt="Secondary language sidebar translation" width="493" height="312" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Secondary-language-sidebar-translation-150x95.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Secondary-language-sidebar-translation-300x190.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Secondary-language-sidebar-translation-1024x650.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 493px) 100vw, 493px" /></a></p>\n<p>7 &#8211; Go to <strong>Appearance &gt; Widgets</strong> and you should be able to see the newly created sidebars. Add desired widgets to the sidebars and make sure you select the language of appearance in each widget you choose. This option is available through the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpml-widgets/">WPML Widgets</a> plugin.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-widgets-to-sidebar.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812615 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-widgets-to-sidebar-300x187.png" alt="Add widgets to sidebar" width="487" height="304" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-widgets-to-sidebar-300x187.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-widgets-to-sidebar-768x480.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Add-widgets-to-sidebar-1024x640.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 487px) 100vw, 487px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Select-language-of-widget.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-812626 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Select-language-of-widget-300x187.png" alt="Select language of widget" width="485" height="302" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #5b94af"><strong>Conclusion:</strong></span></h3>\n<p>WPML, Content Aware Sidebars, and WPML Widgets will give you the option to have different sidebar instances for each language. This is done by setting custom posts for translation and then adding a sidebar in the default language, afterwards translating the custom posts and adding the sidebar in the secondary language. Through this, we can assign widgets to the sidebars created based on the language of the page on which the sidebars are to be displayed.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=nm8j8Un8RVs:qikC2JTKkLU:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=nm8j8Un8RVs:qikC2JTKkLU:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=nm8j8Un8RVs:qikC2JTKkLU:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=nm8j8Un8RVs:qikC2JTKkLU:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=nm8j8Un8RVs:qikC2JTKkLU:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=nm8j8Un8RVs:qikC2JTKkLU:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/nm8j8Un8RVs" heig